<article class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5">
    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">There are many internet marketing agencies and internet marketing firms, but not every agency is the right fit for a local business. A small business usually needs clear advice, practical execution, and measurable improvements.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Look for local experience</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">A local internet marketing agency should understand how customers search in your area. For businesses in Port St. Lucie, Fort Pierce, Stuart, and Vero Beach, local SEO, Google Maps, reviews, and service-area content matter a lot.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Ask what services are actually included</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">When comparing internet marketing services or an internet marketing service near me, ask what the plan includes: website updates, Google Business Profile, SEO, ads, content, reporting, and social media support.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Avoid one-size-fits-all packages</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">The best digital marketing agency near me is not always the biggest one. Local businesses need solutions that match their stage. A new business may need Google and a simple website first. An established business may need PPC advertising and better landing pages.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Choose communication you can understand</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">If an agency cannot explain what they are doing in plain language, that is a warning sign. You should know what is being done, why it matters, and how success will be measured.</p>
      <div class="rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-10 my-12" style="background:var(--primary-lt)">
        <h2 class="text-2xl mb-4" style="color:var(--primary-dk)">Questions to ask before hiring</h2>
        <ul class="checklist mb-0">
          <li>Do you work with local small businesses?</li>
          <li>What will you improve first?</li>
          <li>How do you measure calls, leads, and messages?</li>
          <li>Will I understand the reports?</li>
          <li>Can the plan grow with my business?</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
